  "text": "respectively. Let X (i) be the ith-order statistic of X 1 , . . . , X N . It is easy to see that v N = X (⌈pN ⌉) , where ⌈x⌉ denotes the smallest integer not less than x. Serfling [CITATION_1] showed thatṽ N → v with probability 1 (w.p.1) as N → ∞. If X has a density f (·) in the neighborhood of v and f (v) > 0, Serfling [CITATION_2] further showed thatṽ N is asymptotically normally distributed. More precisely, as",
